![Print friendly, pdf & email](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-03-06T18-30-00-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIxOTQiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCAxOTQgMzAiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIHN0eWxlPSJmaWxsOiNjZmQ0ZGI7ZmlsbC1vcGFjaXR5OiAwLjE7Ii8+PC9zdmc+)A group of Afro-Brazilian slaves has performed for 40 years a series of victorious atecues, with methods similar to the guerrillas, and has upheld the dominant Asculas of the Holy Spirit and in a way to the Empire of Pedroii.

Appearing in S. Mateus, north of the capital Vitória in the 1800s, rebellious Asctions are being considered by historians among the most quilombola struggles in the country, 200 years after Zumbi dos Palmares _(FEARS SOURCES IN PARTS 1 AND 2 OF THIS REPORT)_.

#
####  Scary religion

Headed by Benedito Halida Legua(Inspiring the expression “Will it be obeyed?”), in the northern region of E. Santo, in the Cricaré River Valley, where there are novels from quilombola communities, several black slave made history.

Among them a figure that became legendary, Viriato Cancão-de-Fogo. Cancão is a bird, also known as Bulhian.

It was said that Viriato was only in the darkness, never in the light of day, and it was fearful his powers, for practicing the cabula. This was a Matrizafrican religion, which became frightening for farmers and authorities of the adominant classes.

#
####  Secrets of Islamists

The Cabula was created in Bahia by the capixaba guerrilla Benedito Meia-Legua(Therefore the leader of Viriato)in their disseminating wanderings of the rebellion.

With a syncretist profile, the Cabula was based on secret elements of the Black Malês and the Banto ethnic group(This one brought from Africa/Angola). Ao adotar também uma pitada de influência indígena, éconsiderada às vezes como precursora da umbanda, credo típico do Brasil.

A baiana cabula (also practiced in ES, MG and RJ)It caused panic in the white classes because it had a subversive anti -scrave content in clandestine rituals, invoking warrior ancestral spirits, which came to the mood of the black people to break free and to combat the system that operates.#
####  The Cabula and the Malês Revolt

Although we have not found a record of the presence of the Debenido guerrillas in the famous Bahian evil revolt, the fact that the religion created contains Islamic ingredients shows an obvious bond with the episodebelde in Bahia and the Muslim religion.

The evasive revolt is considered the largest enslaved uprising in the history of Brazil. Word of the Yoruba Language "_Imalê_", which means _ "Muslim" _or _ "Islamic" _, was a popular revolt of enslaved Africans who occurred in the capital Salvador, on January 24, 1835.

The malays were also known as Nagôs in Bahia, a designation given to the Yoruba language speakers on the old slave coast, now part coastal Debenim, Togo and Nigeria.

Islamic nagots had the habit of recording events in Arabic, the sacred tongue of the Muslims. NOTES FOUNDED SERVICE TO UNDERSTAND OSMOTIVE AND BACKGROUND OF THE LIFT. Interestingly, in this case the slaves were more cultured than their owners, mostly illiterate.

#
####  Candomblé with Allah amulets

The revolt, beyond the political and social aspects(End of slavery and freedom won)It also had a very strong religious character. Among the Nagóshavia those who were devotees of the Orishas, Candomblé, although he was in Islam and were mostly Islamists. That is, there was a number of beliefs pour the rebels, even those who followed the guidelines of the Docandomblé, walked with protective amulets of the malays(Muslims).

Nesse encontro das duas religiões (Candomblé and Islam), the Nagôs(MALESE EFFINES OF ORIXÁ)They had a convergence point that was useful for the unit revolt, even without obtaining the objective success.

Due to an anonymous report, the police suffocated the Malê uprising, which although unsuccessful, was very important, and helped weaken the existing slave system in the country.

