# Routes to Metro Manila, paralyzed by ceasefire

Author: Philippine Revolution Web Central

Publish Time: 2023-03-06T92:00:00-04:00

Modified Time: None

Description: An estimated 90% of jeepney routes across Metro Manila have been paralyzed by the ceasefire by drivers of jeepneys and passengers van today. Stop-Past was launched by drivers A

Images: ['[jeepney-phaseout-strike-movement-1024x768.jpeg](https://philippinerevolution.nu/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/jeepney-phaseout-strike-movement-1024x768.jpeg)']

Categories: ["People's Struggles"]

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Philippine Revolution Web Central/2023-03-06T92-00-00-04-00/jeepney-phaseout-strike-movement-1024x768.jpeg )An estimated 90% of the jeepney routes across Metro Manila have been paralyzed by drivers of jeepney and passenger van today. The Past-Past was launched by drivers and operators under the leadership of the unity of chauffeur and operators nationwide(Piston)and the mangenery group. The ceasefire and protest actions will continue in the days.

The ceasefire of democratic organizations, women, youth and other sectors, has been supported. They marched to TungongMendiola in Manila earlier to insist on Marcos Jr.(Puvmp)Government aims to remove passenger jeeps on the road.

Throughout the day, drivers and operators took actions at more than20 protest centers in Metro Manila. Groups also stopped and protested in Bulacan, Pampanga, Rizal, Cavite, Laguna, Albay, Camarines Sur atNorte, Cebu City, Bacolod City and other provinces and cities.

According to the piston, "even other non -piston organizations, are in a state of shock." The group added that despite the police's pressure, state threats, and red-tagging by VP Sara Duterte, "successful ceasefire was successful because of the warm support of the people from various sectors."

In addition to the abolition of false modernization, the PISTON calls for a forced forced construction of cooperatives or corporations and includes it to cancel the independent franchises.

It was announced this afternoon at a media conference by Mody Floranda, President Piston, that they continued to stop and call for a variety of support types for drivers and operators to strike.

Drivers and Operators insisted, they were willing to continue the ceasefire. According to the piston, it was equivalent to a few days when the fight for their livelihood stopped.

