Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Philippine Revolution Web Central/2023-03-06T96-00-00-04-00/charter-change-marcos-photo-from-bulatlat-1024x768.jpeg )The Marcos regime has led the approval of the House of Represenatives Saresolution of Both Houses No. 6 that drives a constitutionalconvention for chacha(charter change)or amendment to the Constitution1987. The 301 "YES" bottles were recorded, while 6 was "no" and one was the abstinence resolution earlier.

The resolution was only passed on the second hearing on February 28. only three days were spent on deliberation representatives.

The only vote in Congress against it was the representatives of the Blocies ACT Teachers Rep. France Castro, Gabriela Rep. ArleneBrosas, and Youth Rep. Raoul Manuel, and three others are Camarines Sur3rd District Rep. Gabriel Bordado, Albay Rep. Edcel Lagman, and Basilan Rep.Mujiv Hataman.

At the same time hearing, groups protested at the House Ofrepresentatives in Quezon City to condemn "Marcos Cha-Cha."

This Charter Change is pushing for a change in provisions in the economy that will further favor the ruling class and provide additional citizens to foreign monopoly capitalists aimed at increasing the country's economy, according to the New Alyansang National Alyan National(Behind).

"Habang nagaganap ang transport strike at krisis sa ekonomya, narito ang mgakongresista, inuuna ang cha-cha para sa dayuhan at iilan. Walang pakundanganat malasakit sa mamamayan. Grabe kayo!" pahayag ni Renato Reyes Jr,pangkalahatang kalihim ng grupong Bayan.

Ayon naman kay Atty. Neri Colmenares, chairperson ng Koalisyong Makabayan,"Kapag polisiyang nagbebenta ng pagmamay-ari sa dayuhan, napakabilis kumilosng Kongreso. Pero kapag mga batas para sa kapakanan ng ordinaryong mamamayantulad ng pagtaas ng pensyon, napakabagal kumilos."

